@NODE introduction "Introduction"

	@{b}Introduction@{ub}

	 Image Descriptor is small program with you can
	 add your own description to images.

	 Well, i know that you can use PPaint or DPaint
	 to do this.

	 But!. Those great programs can`t add description
	 to small brushes and they are not free.

	 Here comes ID. It can add description to any GIF (87a, 89a)
	 and IFF ILBM images.

	 Its very easy and its FREE!

@ENDNODE

@NODE install "Installation"

	@{b}Installation@{ub}

	 Installation is very easy! Just clik on Install icon and install
	 script do all work.

	@{b}Removing@{ub}

	 Removing is easier than installing. Run "Uninstall" program
	 and it remove all ID files.

@ENDNODE


@NODE usage "Usage"

	@{b}How to use Image Descriptor@{ub}

	In main window you see five buttons:

	 @{"" link load } @{b}OPEN@{ub} button	 @{"" link save } @{b}SAVE@{ub} button
	 @{"" link note } @{b}NOTE@{ub} button   @{"" link info } @{b}INFO@{ub} button
	 @{"" link view } @{b}VIEW@{ub} button   @{"" link about } @{b}ABOUT@{ub} button

	Select button for more information about it ..

@ENDNODE

@NODE load "Loading images"

	@{b}Loading images...@{ub}

	 After clicking on this button a file requester
	 will appear.
	 You can select file for load.

	 Default #?.(GIF|IFF|ILBM) pattern is set but you
	 can change it and load file with any name.

	 IF it wasn`t valid image or if you dont have
	 enought memory to load that file ID will inform
	 you about it.

@ENDNODE

@NODE save "Saving images..."

	@{b}Saving images...@{ub}

	 After clicking on this button a file requester
	 will appear.
	 You can select file and ID will write image
	 to this file.

	 If you select file already exists ID lets you
	 choose to overwrite it or to select other file.

	 A File Comment will be writed with this file
	 contains descriptiom added to image.
	 If description is longer than 75 characters
	 ID will cut it and add " ..." at the end of
	 File Comment.

@ENDNODE

@NODE view "View image"

	@{b}Viewing images@{ub}

	 This is new in v1.4.3.
	 When you select this button ID will load MultiView with
	 path of image loaded into memory.

	 This button may be disabled in this situations:
	  - MultiView is not present in C: drawer (it must be here
	    becouse ID look there for it)
	  - ILBM or GIF datatype is not installed.

	 If you done watching just quit MultiView and you
	 will back to ID.

	NOTE:
	  MultiView is NOT included with ID.

@ENDNODE

@NODE info "Image information"

	@{b}Image information...@{ub}

	 After clicking on this button you see
	 a window with few informations.

	 You may found that two different windows
	 are open.

	 If ID have in memory GIF image it shows
	 you info about GIF.
	 IF it is ILBM you see info about ILBM.

	 Why two windows?
	 Its simple. GIF and ILBM are very different
	 images. ILBM images don`t have progressive
	 displaying and dont have transparency index.
	 GIF images dont have bitplanes.

	 But few informations are the same.
	 Like:
	  - image size
	  - screen size
	  - position

	 The last information is about datatypes.
	 If ID can`t finds datatypes, VIEW option
	 will be disabled.

@ENDNODE

@NODE note "Image description"

	@{b}Image description@{ub}

	 After clicking on this buttons a small
	 window will appear asking you for your note.

	 Like in @{" INFO " link info } mode, here
	 you may also see two different windows.

	 If you load ILBM image you may now choose
	 few things.

	 @{i}Annotation@{ui} - clicking here your
	 note will be added as annotation.

	 @{i}Name@{ui} - clicking here your
	 note will be added as image name.

	 @{i}Author@{ui} - clicking here your
	 note will be added as author name.

	 @{i}Copyrights@{ui} - clicking here your
	 note will be added as copyrights info.

	 If you load GIF image you can add note
	 without choosing its type.

@ENDNODE

